        "content": "<p>I have proven that <code>F x y z = F x z y</code> and <code>F x y z = F y x z</code>, and I want to show that <code>F</code> is always constant regardless of order of parameters. Is there a tag to automatically generate all five theorem given these two? Or I have to write down all five theorems every single time?</p>\n<p>(I'm not native speaker and this is the first time I join the community, so forgive me If I've done something wrong.)</p>",
        "id": 459448026,
        "sender_full_name": "yummy",
        "timestamp": 1723203178
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we have anything there; do you have multiple such <code>F</code>s?</p>",
